info.headline: Flood Advisory issued July 23 at 3:30PM CDT until July 23 at 4:45PM CDT by NWS Duluth MN
info.description:
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.
* WHERE...In Wisconsin, Burnett County.
* WHEN...Until 445 PM CDT Wednesday.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. Ponding of water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 330 PM CDT Wednesday, the public reported flooding in the advisory area. Between 1 and 3 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts up to 1 inch are expected over the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Grantsburg, Trade Lake, Siren, Webster, Webb Lake Wisconsin, Saint Croix Band Clam Lake Area, Saint Croix Band Pike Lake area, Danbury, Saint Croix Band Sand Lake Area, Hertel, Saint Croix Band Bashaw area, Branstad, Randall, Oakland, Clam Lake near Siren, Yellow Lake, Falun, Big Sand Lake, Saint Croix Band Danbury area and Alpha. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood.
info.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
Report observed flooding to local emergency services or law enforcement and to the National Weather Service in Duluth when you can do so safely. Flooding can be reported to the National Weather Service at 1-800-685-8612.
